{#-
Concept card page skeleton (Program 24 P2 WO-36; Constitution III.13).

Static game-theory reference content, not a per-tick observation — no
verified_tick staleness stamp (see babylon.projection.vault.concept_cards
module docstring: a mathematical definition does not go stale the way a
committed-tick observation does). Every ConceptCard field is always present
by construction, so — unlike county.md.j2 — this template touches the view
model's attributes directly rather than through precomputed
statblock_rows/absent_fields: there is no Optional field here that could be
None, so Jinja's StrictUndefined has nothing to trip on.

Fenced directives: {statblock} only, matching
babylon.tui.directives.BabylonFence dispatch (ADR099: paired containers
break the 8.2.8 markdown walker). The statblock body is always baked (never
live) — a ConceptCard has no runtime provider to defer to.
-#}
---
id: concept/{{ card.slug }}
name: {{ card.title }}
kind: concept-card
citation: {{ card.citation }}
---

# concept/{{ card.slug }} — {{ card.title }}

{{ card.statement }}

{% if card.formula is not none -%}
```
{{ card.formula }}
```
{% endif %}
```{statblock} concept/{{ card.slug }}
{% for term in card.terms -%}
{{ term.label }}: {{ term.meaning }}
{% endfor -%}
```

{% if card.implementation -%}
## Implementation

{% for ref in card.implementation -%}
- `{{ ref }}`
{% endfor %}
{% endif -%}
{% if card.see_also -%}
## See also

{% for slug in card.see_also -%}
- [[concept/{{ slug }}]]
{% endfor %}
{% endif -%}
